definition.value: A N-methyl-L-alpha-amino acid  that is the N(alpha)-methyl derivative of L-tryptophan.
A monomethoxyflavone that is the 4'-methyl ether derivative of apigenin.
An amino trisaccharide comprised of alpha-neuraminic acid, beta-D-galactopyranose and D-glucopyranose residues linked sequentially (2->6) and (1->4).

An amino nonasaccharide derivative that is beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc in which the mannosyl group is substituted at positions 3 and 6 by beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man groups, while the D-GlcNAc carries two L-Fuc residues attached via alpha-(1->3)- and alpha-(1->6)-linkages.
A poly(glycerol phosphate) having an alanyl group attached to the hydroxy function of the repeating unit.
